{"cursor":"13441","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Defunct Company\n| company_name = Black Isle Studios company_logo = fate = foundation = 1996\n| defunct = location = Orange County, California, USA key_people = Feargus\n| Urquhart, Chris Avellone, Darren Monahan, Brian Mitsoda, Chris Jones (1996-\n| 2003)  Chris Taylor (2012-now) industry = Video games industry products =\n| Video games parent = Interplay Entertainment revenue = operating_income =\n| net_income = num_employees = homepage = status = Subsidary homepage =\n| [http://www.blackisle.com// www.blackisle.com]\n}}\n\n'Black Isle Studios' is a division of the computer and video game developer and\npublisher Interplay Entertainment. Black Isle Studios is a division that\ndevelops role-playing video games, and it previously published several games\nfrom other developers.\n\nBlack Isle is based in Orange County, California, USA. The division\nwas formed in 1996, adopting the name \"Black Isle Studios\" in 1998. The idea for the division's name came from the Black\nIsle in Scotland - founder Feargus Urquhart's native country. Black Isle Studios is most famous for working on the\nfirst two games in the popular and influential [[Fallout (series)|Fallout]]\nseries as well as the critically acclaimed [[Planescape: Torment]]. They also\nachieved success with the [[Icewind Dale]] and [[Baldur's Gate]] series of role-\nplaying video games, though they only published the Baldur's Gate series. In\n1999, IGN's RPG Vault gave it the award for a Developer Of The Year. [http:-\n//web.archive.org/web/200102042117/http://rpgvault.ign.com/features/specials/aw-\nards99.shtml 1999 Vault Network Awards]\n\nOn August 22, 2012, Interplay, after releasing [[MDK2#MDK2 HD|MDK2 HD]] on Steam\nwould revive the studio with the motto \"Our goal has always been to make the\nworld's best RPGs\" and the slogan \"Black Isle is Back\".\n","linknr":306,"url":"Black_Isle_Studios","recorded":1376419813,"links":["/w/inde